MBOMBELA – Three leaners from this school made it to the top ten , one of which was the overall best learner, Natasha Agostinho following the release of the grade 12 results. As such, Malaza used the occasion to officially confirm the Provincial Bursary to all three learners and officially handover of a brand new Toyota Aygo to Agostinho which was sponsored by Freedom Stationery. Malaza said overall, their department was encouraged by the good start after teaching systems  were put in place for this year to commence. 